mibVersion.name: mibVersion
mibVersion.description: The version number of this FRX MIB.

mibEditVersion.name: mibEditVersion
mibEditVersion.description: The edit version (sub version) number of this FRX MIB.

nodeIdnxAddress.name: nodeIdnxAddress
nodeIdnxAddress.description: The IDNX Address of this PX card, e.g. NxCy.

nodeSoftwareRelease.name: nodeSoftwareRelease
nodeSoftwareRelease.description: The release of FRX code running on this PX card, e.g. Release 2.01.01 Version 81.01.

nodeSoftwareReleaseDate.name: nodeSoftwareReleaseDate
nodeSoftwareReleaseDate.description: The date the FRX code was built, e.g. Wed Feb 10 14:12:24 PST 1993 by tee.

nodeBootVersion.name: nodeBootVersion
nodeBootVersion.description: The version of boot prom on the PX card.

nodeCardType.name: nodeCardType
nodeCardType.description: The type of PX card running the FRX code.

nodeUpTime.name: nodeUpTime
nodeUpTime.description: The amount of time the FRX has been alive.

nodeCongestionLevel.name: nodeCongestionLevel
nodeCongestionLevel.description: The current state of congestion for the FRX node. The valid values are notCongested (normal operation), approachingCongestion (FECN and BECN are being set), congested (DE frames are being dropped), and fullyCongested (normal data frames are being dropped).

nodeBuffersUsed.name: nodeBuffersUsed
nodeBuffersUsed.description: The number of system buffers being used.

nodeNumberHDLCPorts.name: nodeNumberHDLCPorts
nodeNumberHDLCPorts.description: The number of HDLC ports the hardware supports.

nodeIPAddress.name: nodeIPAddress
nodeIPAddress.description: The IP Address of this FRX Node.

nodeNetworkMask.name: nodeNetworkMask
nodeNetworkMask.description: The IP network mask for this FRX Node.

nodeBackcard.name: nodeBackcard
nodeBackcard.description: Enables or disables the backcard on the FRX node. The backcard must be enabled for gateway functionality. Note: If the backcard is not physically present, an attempt to enable it will result in an error.

nodeBackcardType.name: nodeBackcardType
nodeBackcardType.description: The type of backcard interface installed.

nodeBackcardSerialNumber.name: nodeBackcardSerialNumber
nodeBackcardSerialNumber.description: The serial number and revision of the backcard interface.

nodeBillingDownloads.name: nodeBillingDownloads
nodeBillingDownloads.description: Enables or disables billing record downloads to an NMS workstation from this FRX node.

nodeConfigurationDownloads.name: nodeConfigurationDownloads
nodeConfigurationDownloads.description: Enables or disables configuration record downloads to an NMS workstation from this FRX node.

nodeFrameCounterThreshold.name: nodeFrameCounterThreshold
nodeFrameCounterThreshold.description: A threshold that causes a billing record to be downloaded when a frame counter exceeds its value.

nodeByteCounterThreshold.name: nodeByteCounterThreshold
nodeByteCounterThreshold.description: A threshold that causes a billing record to be downloaded when a byte counter exceeds its value.

nodeBillingTimeTable.name: nodeBillingTimeTable
nodeBillingTimeTable.description: The list of times to download billing records to an NMS workstation.

nodeNMSWorkstationTable.name: nodeNMSWorkstationTable
nodeNMSWorkstationTable.description: The list of workstations that are downloaded with billing and configuration records.

nodeNumberTBUSPorts.name: nodeNumberTBUSPorts
nodeNumberTBUSPorts.description: The number of TBus ports the hardware supports.

nodeBackcardWanIF.name: nodeBackcardWanIF
nodeBackcardWanIF.description: Enables or disables the backcard WAN I/F on the FRX node. The backcard must be enabled for WAN port functionality. Note: If the backcard is not physically present, an attempt to enable it will result in an error.

nodeAlarmedPorts.name: nodeAlarmedPorts
nodeAlarmedPorts.description: The number of front or backcard ports on this node where any of the following conditions is true: - portTBusState (or T1 Status for backcard ports) is 'down' - portUNIState is 'down' - portAlarmedPVCs is not zero.

nodeBackcardHardwareAddress.name: nodeBackcardHardwareAddress
nodeBackcardHardwareAddress.description: The hardware address of the backcard interface.

nodeBillingTimeEntry.name: nodeBillingTimeEntry
nodeBillingTimeEntry.description: A row from the billing download time table.

downloadTime.name: downloadTime
downloadTime.description: A time of day at which billing records for the node are sent to an NMS workstation.

downloadTimeRowStatus.name: downloadTimeRowStatus
downloadTimeRowStatus.description: Controls row deletion for this table. Setting to invalid deletes the row from the table.

downloadTimeIndex.name: downloadTimeIndex
downloadTimeIndex.description: The index into the billing time table.

nodeNMSWorkstationEntry.name: nodeNMSWorkstationEntry
nodeNMSWorkstationEntry.description: A row from the NMS workstation download target list.

nmsWorkstationAddress.name: nmsWorkstationAddress
nmsWorkstationAddress.description: The IP address of an NMS workstation that billing and configuration records get downloaded to.

nmsWorkstationInetPort.name: nmsWorkstationInetPort
nmsWorkstationInetPort.description: The internet port on which the special TFTP server on an NMS workstation will listen for requests to download billing and configuration records.

nmsWorkstationRowStatus.name: nmsWorkstationRowStatus
nmsWorkstationRowStatus.description: Controls row deletion for this table. Setting to invalid deletes the row from the table.

portConfTable.name: portConfTable
portConfTable.description: A table of this FRX's port configuration. Before attempting to modify any variables in this table, the port must be disabled (set portConfState = 'disable').

portConfEntry.name: portConfEntry
portConfEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the port configuration table.

portConfEntryId.name: portConfEntryId
portConfEntryId.description: The port identifier (number) for this port.

portConfState.name: portConfState
portConfState.description: Performs the enumerated action on the port. That is to say, setting the value to delete will cause the port to be deleted, etc. This variable must be set to 'disable' before any other port configuration variables can be modified.

portInterfaceProtocol.name: portInterfaceProtocol
portInterfaceProtocol.description: Determines the function of the port, including which UNI protocol is to be used. All values except interNode are for ports at access points into the network. InterNode is for ports internal to the network. AnsiNetwork, ansiUser, and ansiNNI conform to procedures specified in the ANSI T1.617 Annex D specification. ccittNetwork, ccittUser, and ccittNNI conform to procedures specified in the CCITT Q.933 Annex A specification. lmiNetwork, lmiUser, and lmiNNI conform to procedures specified in the DEC, Northern Telecom, StratCom specification.

portKeepaliveVerif.name: portKeepaliveVerif
portKeepaliveVerif.description: Enables or disables keepalive verification. This parameter is applicable when the portInterfaceProtocol is interNode.

portBackupInterNodal.name: portBackupInterNodal
portBackupInterNodal.description: Enables or disables using this port as a backup Inter-Nodal port. This parameter is applicable when the portInterfaceProtocol is interNode.

portExternalFrTrunk.name: portExternalFrTrunk
portExternalFrTrunk.description: Enables or disables the External Frame Relay Trunk feature.

portUniExternalFrTrunk.name: portUniExternalFrTrunk
portUniExternalFrTrunk.description: The UNI protocol to use when the External Frame Relay Trunk feature is enabled.

portDlciExternalFrTrunk.name: portDlciExternalFrTrunk
portDlciExternalFrTrunk.description: The DLCI of the PVC that is in use at the UNI when the External Frame Relay Trunk feature is enabled.

portLinkIntegVerif.name: portLinkIntegVerif
portLinkIntegVerif.description: Determines whether this port will react to problems detected by a UNI protocol. This parameter is applicable if the portInterfaceProtocol is ansi*, ccitt*, or lmi*.

portAsyncPVCStatus.name: portAsyncPVCStatus
portAsyncPVCStatus.description: Determines whether this port should send Asynchronous PVC status messages. This parameter is applicable if the portInterfaceProtocol is ansiNetwork, ansiNNI, ccittNetwork, or ccittNNI.

portN391Counter.name: portN391Counter
portN391Counter.description: The value for N391, the full status polling counter.

portN392Counter.name: portN392Counter
portN392Counter.description: The value for N392, the error threshold counter.

portN393Counter.name: portN393Counter
portN393Counter.description: The value for N393, the monitored events counter.

portT391Timer.name: portT391Timer
portT391Timer.description: The value for T391, the link integrity polling timer.

portT392Timer.name: portT392Timer
portT392Timer.description: The value for T392, the polling verification timer.

portSdlcEncapMode.name: portSdlcEncapMode
portSdlcEncapMode.description: Selects which encapsulation mode to be used when the portInterfacePrococol is sdlcHdlcEncap.

portSdlcEncapDefaultDlci.name: portSdlcEncapDefaultDlci
portSdlcEncapDefaultDlci.description: Specifies which DLCI will be used to encapsulate received SDLC/HDLC frames at the entry to the network. This parameter is applicable if the portInterfaceProtocol is sdlcHdlcEncap and the encapsulation mode is transparent.

portAddrMapDefaultDlci.name: portAddrMapDefaultDlci
portAddrMapDefaultDlci.description: Specifies which DLCI will be used to encapsulate received SDLC/HDLC frames at the entry to the network. This parameter is applicable if the portInterfaceProtocol is sdlcHdlcEncap and the encapsulation mode is address-mapped.

portPriorityQueuing.name: portPriorityQueuing
portPriorityQueuing.description: Enables or disables priority queuing on a port.

portAccountingPerDlci.name: portAccountingPerDlci
portAccountingPerDlci.description: Enables or disables accounting per DLCI on a port. Enabling this feature may seriously degrade performance in systems with high speed (greater than 1.024 Mbps) ports. Frames may be lost.

portPVCOptimization.name: portPVCOptimization
portPVCOptimization.description: Enables or disables route optimization per DLCI on a port. Enabling this feature may seriously degrade performance in systems with high speed (greater than 1.024 Mbps) ports. Frames may be lost.

portStatusTable.name: portStatusTable
portStatusTable.description: A table of this node's port status and statistics.

portStatusEntry.name: portStatusEntry
portStatusEntry.description: The port status and statistics table.

portDataBaseState.name: portDataBaseState
portDataBaseState.description: The state of the port in the database. The values are active and disabled.

portTBusState.name: portTBusState
portTBusState.description: The state of the TBus connection for this port. The values are up and down.

portUNIState.name: portUNIState
portUNIState.description: The state of the UNI for this port. The valid values are up and down.

portNumberEstablishedCircuits.name: portNumberEstablishedCircuits
portNumberEstablishedCircuits.description: The number of virtual circuits on this port in state Complete.

portNumberTotalCircuits.name: portNumberTotalCircuits
portNumberTotalCircuits.description: The total number of virtual circuits on this port, regardles of state.

portRxCongestState.name: portRxCongestState
portRxCongestState.description: The congestion state of the port's receiver. The valid values are notCongested (normal operation), approachingCongestion (FECN and BECN are being set), congested (DE frames are being dropped), and fullyCongested (normal data frames are being dropped).

portTxCongestState.name: portTxCongestState
portTxCongestState.description: The congestion state of the port's transmitter. The valid values are notCongested (normal operation), approachingCongestion (FECN and BECN are being set), congested (DE frames are being dropped), and fullyCongested (normal data frames are being dropped).

portAccessRate.name: portAccessRate
portAccessRate.description: The access rate (speed) for this port in bits per second.

portCIR.name: portCIR
portCIR.description: The total allocated committed information rate for all virtual circuits on this port.

portNeighbor.name: portNeighbor
portNeighbor.description: Represents the IDNX domain-node-card of the adjacent FRX. This field is valid for ports with the interface protocol set to interNode.

portInFrames.name: portInFrames
portInFrames.description: The number of frames received by this port.

portOutFrames.name: portOutFrames
portOutFrames.description: The number of frames transmitter by this port.

portInBytes.name: portInBytes
portInBytes.description: The number of bytes received by this port.

portOutBytes.name: portOutBytes
portOutBytes.description: The number of bytes transmitted by this port.

portDroppedFrames.name: portDroppedFrames
portDroppedFrames.description: The number of frames dropped by the port for reasons other than: DE, unknown DLCI, bandwidth admission, input/output congestion, frame error, inactive PVC, or disabled port. These are generally internal errors, such as 'Heap buffer failed'.

portDroppedDEFrames.name: portDroppedDEFrames
portDroppedDEFrames.description: The number of frames with DE set dropped due to congestion.

portUnknownDLCIFrames.name: portUnknownDLCIFrames
portUnknownDLCIFrames.description: The number of frames received with unknown DLCIs.

portLastUnknownDLCI.name: portLastUnknownDLCI
portLastUnknownDLCI.description: The DLCI number of the last frame with an unknown DLCI. A value of -1 signifies that no unknown DLCI has yet been received.

portDEInFrames.name: portDEInFrames
portDEInFrames.description: The number of DE frames received by a port.

portDEOutFrames.name: portDEOutFrames
portDEOutFrames.description: The number of DE frames transmitted by a port.

portDEInBytes.name: portDEInBytes
portDEInBytes.description: The number of bytes received in DE frames.

portDEOutBytes.name: portDEOutBytes
portDEOutBytes.description: The number of bytes transmitted in DE frames.

portBECNInFrames.name: portBECNInFrames
portBECNInFrames.description: The number of BECN frames received by a port.

portBECNOutFrames.name: portBECNOutFrames
portBECNOutFrames.description: The number BECN frames transmitted by a port.

portFECNInFrames.name: portFECNInFrames
portFECNInFrames.description: The number of FECN frames received by a port.

portFECNOutFrames.name: portFECNOutFrames
portFECNOutFrames.description: The number of FECN frames transmitted by a port.

portFrameRateIn.name: portFrameRateIn
portFrameRateIn.description: The rate in frames per second of frames received by the FRX. This number is a updated every minute and represents the last five minutes worth of traffic.

portFrameRateOut.name: portFrameRateOut
portFrameRateOut.description: The rate in frames per second of frames transmitted by the FRX. This number is a updated every minute and represents the last five minutes worth of traffic.

portByteRateIn.name: portByteRateIn
portByteRateIn.description: The rate in bytes per second received by the FRX. This number is updated every minute and represents the last five minutes worth of traffic.

portByteRateOut.name: portByteRateOut
portByteRateOut.description: The rate in bytes per second received by the FRX. This number is updated every minute and represents the last five minutes worth of traffic.

portAverageRxQueue.name: portAverageRxQueue
portAverageRxQueue.description: The average depth of the receiver's input queue.

portAverageTxQueue.name: portAverageTxQueue
portAverageTxQueue.description: The average depth of the transmitter's output queue.

portMaxFrameRateIn.name: portMaxFrameRateIn
portMaxFrameRateIn.description: The maximum frame rate for frames received by a port.

portMaxFrameRateOut.name: portMaxFrameRateOut
portMaxFrameRateOut.description: The maximum frame rate for frames transmitted by a port.

portMaxByteRateIn.name: portMaxByteRateIn
portMaxByteRateIn.description: The maximum byte rate for frames received by a port.

portMaxByteRateOut.name: portMaxByteRateOut
portMaxByteRateOut.description: The maximum byte rate for frames transmitted by a port.

portMaxQueueDepthIn.name: portMaxQueueDepthIn
portMaxQueueDepthIn.description: The maximum length of a port's receive queue.

portMaxQueueDepthOut.name: portMaxQueueDepthOut
portMaxQueueDepthOut.description: The maximum length of a port's transmit queue.

portBadFrames.name: portBadFrames
portBadFrames.description: The number of frames dropped by the HDLC controller. Examples of reasons why frames are dropped include receiving a bad CRC and non-octet alignment.

portShortFrames.name: portShortFrames
portShortFrames.description: The number of frames received by the HDLC controller that don't meet the minimum length restriction.

portMissedFrames.name: portMissedFrames
portMissedFrames.description: The number of receive frames missed by the HDLC controller. This happens when the receiver's input queue is full.

portLongFrames.name: portLongFrames
portLongFrames.description: The number of frames received longer than the maximum length.

portRxOverruns.name: portRxOverruns
portRxOverruns.description: The number of receiver overruns the HDLC controller experiences.

portTxUnderruns.name: portTxUnderruns
portTxUnderruns.description: The number of transmitter underruns the HDLC controller experiences.

portStatusEntryId.name: portStatusEntryId
portStatusEntryId.description: The port identifier (number) for this port.

portStatsClearedTime.name: portStatsClearedTime
portStatsClearedTime.description: The amount of time since the last time the statistics were cleared for this port.

portDropBWadmitFrames.name: portDropBWadmitFrames
portDropBWadmitFrames.description: The number of frames dropped due to Bandwidth Admission enforcement at the port. This occurs when the number of frames is greater than (Bc + Be) during Tc over all Tc's since the last clear of statistics. In other words, these are the burst frames which exceed the sum of the Committed Burst size (Bc) and the Excess Burst size (Be) over each time interval (Tc). This count is only valid when Bandwidth Admission is Enabled for the port; otherwise, it is zero.

portDropInCongestFrames.name: portDropInCongestFrames
portDropInCongestFrames.description: The number of frames dropped because the port input buffer is fully congested.

portDropOutCongestFrames.name: portDropOutCongestFrames
portDropOutCongestFrames.description: The number of frames dropped because the port output buffer is fully congested.

portDropErroredFrames.name: portDropErroredFrames
portDropErroredFrames.description: The number of frames dropped because of frame errors. These include: bad DLCI, invalid DLCI (with and without Cache), invalid source route frame, and wierd frame.

portDropPVCinactiveFrames.name: portDropPVCinactiveFrames
portDropPVCinactiveFrames.description: The number of frames dropped because the PVC is inactive.

portDropPortDisabledFrames.name: portDropPortDisabledFrames
portDropPortDisabledFrames.description: The number of frames dropped because the port is Disabled.

portChannelAssignment.name: portChannelAssignment
portChannelAssignment.description: This variable will not be available from version 3.0 onwards; it has been replaced by portChannelAssignment30 (see below).

portAlarmedPVCs.name: portAlarmedPVCs
portAlarmedPVCs.description: The number of circuits on this port where all of the following conditions are true: - circuitState is not 'idle' - circuitStatus is not 'active'.

portChannelAssignment30.name: portChannelAssignment30
portChannelAssignment30.description: The DS0s assigned to this logical backcard port. These may, or may not, be contiguous (when more than one is assigned).

portSdlcEncapMapTable.name: portSdlcEncapMapTable
portSdlcEncapMapTable.description: The table containing address map translations between DLCIs and SDLC/HDLC addresses. This table is applicable if the portInterfaceProtocol is sdlcHdlcEncap and the portSdlcEncapMode is addressMapped.

portSdlcEncapMapEntry.name: portSdlcEncapMapEntry
portSdlcEncapMapEntry.description: A row from the address map translation table.

addressMapSdlcAddress.name: addressMapSdlcAddress
addressMapSdlcAddress.description: The SDLC or HDLC address that is mapped to a DLCI when using SDLC/HDLC encapsulation.

addressMapDlci.name: addressMapDlci
addressMapDlci.description: The DLCI used when mapping an SCLC/HDLC address when SLDC/HDLC encapsulation is being used.

addressMapRowStatus.name: addressMapRowStatus
addressMapRowStatus.description: Used to create a row in the table.

addressMapPortNumber.name: addressMapPortNumber
addressMapPortNumber.description: The port number index for the address map table.

circuitConfTable.name: circuitConfTable
circuitConfTable.description: A table containing configuration information for a circuit. The objects in this table are always readable; they can only be written (if accessible) only for the instance in which the circuitConfPortNumber and circuitConfDLCI correspond to the port number and DLCI at the source (originate). When creating a new circuit, at a minimum the destination address must be supplied. Note: Before modifying any circuit configuration variables, the circuit must be disabled (set circuitConfState = 'disable').

circuitConfEntry.name: circuitConfEntry
circuitConfEntry.description: Configuration information about a particular circuit.

circuitSourceAddress.name: circuitSourceAddress
circuitSourceAddress.description: The value of this object is the source (originate) address of this circuit. It is expressed in terms of IDNX Node, Card, and Port (NxCyPz).

circuitSourceDLCI.name: circuitSourceDLCI
circuitSourceDLCI.description: The value of this object is the DLCI associated with the source address of this circuit.

circuitDestinationAddress.name: circuitDestinationAddress
circuitDestinationAddress.description: The value of this object is the destination (termination) address of this circuit. The value must be consistent with the endpoint of the user-selected path (if one exists). In the case of a manager that can issue only single-varbind Set requests, clear the user-selected path (if one exists) before attempting to change this value.

circuitDestinationDLCI.name: circuitDestinationDLCI
circuitDestinationDLCI.description: The value of this object is the DLCI associated with the destination address of this circuit.

circuitUserSelectedPath.name: circuitUserSelectedPath
circuitUserSelectedPath.description: The value of this object is the required path through the FRX network that this virtual circuit must take. The endpoints of this path must be consistent with the configured source and destination addresses. The value 'disabled' indicates that a user-selected path has not been configured.

circuitAllowAlternatePath.name: circuitAllowAlternatePath
circuitAllowAlternatePath.description: If a user-selected path has been configured, enabling this variable allows the FRX to choose an alternate route through the network if the user-selected path is unavailable. Disabling it forces the FRX to wait until the user-selected path is available before establishing the PVC.

circuitBandwidthAdmission.name: circuitBandwidthAdmission
circuitBandwidthAdmission.description: The field reflects the status of bandwidth admission for this virtual circuit. If enabled then CIR, Be, and Bc must be configured.

circuitCommittedInfoRate.name: circuitCommittedInfoRate
circuitCommittedInfoRate.description: The committed information rate (in bits per second) for this virtual circuit.

circuitBurstSize.name: circuitBurstSize
circuitBurstSize.description: The burst size (Bc, expressed in bits) for this virtual circuit.

circuitExcessBurstSize.name: circuitExcessBurstSize
circuitExcessBurstSize.description: The excess burst size (Be, expressed in bits) for this virtual circuit.

circuitPriority.name: circuitPriority
circuitPriority.description: The priority value of this circuit. If prioritized circuits are not enabled on the port then the circuit priority is set to (normal); normal priority is always one less than the highest priority available, which depend on the number of priority queues defined. There can between 2, and 15 priority queues defined. The default is 3. This parameter can not be set unless Prioritize PVC is enabled for the port (portPriorityQueueing).

circuitConfState.name: circuitConfState
circuitConfState.description: The database state for this virtual circuit. Setting this field to delete causes the virtual circuit to be deleted. Setting this field to install either creates a new circuit, or disables an already existing circuit. Activating the circuit builds the circuit across the network. Note: The database state must be set to 'disable' before any other circuit parameters can be modified.

circuitConfPortNumber.name: circuitConfPortNumber
circuitConfPortNumber.description: The first index into the circuit configuration table.

circuitConfDLCI.name: circuitConfDLCI
circuitConfDLCI.description: The second index into the circuit configuration table.

circuitStatusTable.name: circuitStatusTable
circuitStatusTable.description: A table containing virtual circuit status for this port

circuitStatusEntry.name: circuitStatusEntry
circuitStatusEntry.description: A status entry contains information about virtual circuits.

circuitDataBaseState.name: circuitDataBaseState
circuitDataBaseState.description: The value of this object identifies the current database state of the PVC.

circuitState.name: circuitState
circuitState.description: This field represents the status of the virtual circuit. The possible values for the state are idle, setup, complete, and disconnect.

circuitSetupFailureReason.name: circuitSetupFailureReason
circuitSetupFailureReason.description: This field is valid when the call cannot be completed. The reason the circuit setup failed is contained in this string.

circuitLastDisconnectReason.name: circuitLastDisconnectReason
circuitLastDisconnectReason.description: This field displays the reason for the last disconnect of this virtual circuit, including normal termination.

circuitRoute.name: circuitRoute
circuitRoute.description: This field displays the route that the circuit has taken through the FRX network. It is expressed in terms of IDNX Nodes and Cards (NxCy-NxCy-[...]NxCy.)

circuitWindowLength.name: circuitWindowLength
circuitWindowLength.description: The value of this object is the window length (Tc) used for bandwidth admission procedures. The units are tenths-of-seconds. This object is applicable only if bandwidth admission is enabled for the circuit.

circuitReceiveFrames.name: circuitReceiveFrames
circuitReceiveFrames.description: The number of frames received by this circuit.

circuitTransmitFrames.name: circuitTransmitFrames
circuitTransmitFrames.description: The number of frames transmitted by this circuit.

circuitReceiveBytes.name: circuitReceiveBytes
circuitReceiveBytes.description: The number of bytes received by this circuit.

circuitTransmitBytes.name: circuitTransmitBytes
circuitTransmitBytes.description: The number of bytes transmitted by this circuit.

circuitDroppedFrames.name: circuitDroppedFrames
circuitDroppedFrames.description: This field represents the number of frames dropped for this DLCI due to bandwidth admission procedures.

circuitMarkedDEFrames.name: circuitMarkedDEFrames
circuitMarkedDEFrames.description: This field represents the number of frames in which the FRX set the DE bit, due to bandwidth admission procedures.

circuitReceivedDEFrames.name: circuitReceivedDEFrames
circuitReceivedDEFrames.description: This field represents the number of frames received with the DE bit set.

circuitCurrentTcBurstBits.name: circuitCurrentTcBurstBits
circuitCurrentTcBurstBits.description: The number of Bc bits received during the present Tc window.

circuitCurrentTcExcessBits.name: circuitCurrentTcExcessBits
circuitCurrentTcExcessBits.description: The number of Be bits received during the present Tc window.

circuitMaximumBcBits.name: circuitMaximumBcBits
circuitMaximumBcBits.description: The maximum number of Bc bits received for this virtual circuit.

circuitMaximumBeBits.name: circuitMaximumBeBits
circuitMaximumBeBits.description: The maximum number of Be bits received for this virtual circuit.

circuitAverageBc.name: circuitAverageBc
circuitAverageBc.description: The average number of Bc bits during the past five (5) Tc periods.

circuitAverageBe.name: circuitAverageBe
circuitAverageBe.description: The average number of Be bits during the past five (5) Tc periods.

circuitStatus.name: circuitStatus
circuitStatus.description: The status of virtual circuit. The valid values are Active or Inactive.

circuitDownReason.name: circuitDownReason
circuitDownReason.description: This field is a description of why the virtual circuit is down.

circuitBECNReceiveFrames.name: circuitBECNReceiveFrames
circuitBECNReceiveFrames.description: The number of BECN frames received by the circuit.

circuitBECNTransmitFrames.name: circuitBECNTransmitFrames
circuitBECNTransmitFrames.description: The number of BECN frames transmitted by the circuit.

circuitFECNReceiveFrames.name: circuitFECNReceiveFrames
circuitFECNReceiveFrames.description: The number of FECN frames received by the circuit.

circuitFECNTransmitFrames.name: circuitFECNTransmitFrames
circuitFECNTransmitFrames.description: The number of FECN frames transmitted by the circuit.

circuitStatusPortNumber.name: circuitStatusPortNumber
circuitStatusPortNumber.description: The first index into the circuit table.

circuitStatusDLCI.name: circuitStatusDLCI
circuitStatusDLCI.description: The second index into the circuit table.

circuitSrcSidePort.name: circuitSrcSidePort
circuitSrcSidePort.description: A circuit segment within an FRX node has two endpoints, each identified by a (port,DLCI) pair. This variable is the source side port number. Note: A value of -1 means 'not applicable'. This variable is not applicable unless the PVC state is Complete.

circuitSrcSideDLCI.name: circuitSrcSideDLCI
circuitSrcSideDLCI.description: A circuit segment within an FRX node has two endpoints, each identified by a (port,DLCI) pair. This variable is the source side DLCI. Note: A value of -1 means 'not applicable'. This variable is not applicable unless the PVC state is Complete.

circuitDestSidePort.name: circuitDestSidePort
circuitDestSidePort.description: A circuit segment within an FRX node has two endpoints, each identified by a (port,DLCI) pair. This variable is the destination side port number. Note: A value of -1 means 'not applicable'. This variable is not applicable unless the PVC state is Complete.

circuitDestSideDLCI.name: circuitDestSideDLCI
circuitDestSideDLCI.description: A circuit segment within an FRX node has two endpoints, each identified by a (port,DLCI) pair. This variable is the destination side DLCI. Note: A value of -1 means 'not applicable'. This variable is not applicable unless the PVC state is Complete.

operatorCount.name: operatorCount
operatorCount.description: The number of operators currently installed on this FRX.

operatorTable.name: operatorTable
operatorTable.description: The list of operators installed on this FRX. A row can be added to this table using a set request that includes, at minimum, a valid value for operatorIdentifier. A row can be deleted by setting operatorRowStatus to invalid.

operatorTableEntry.name: operatorTableEntry
operatorTableEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the operator table.

operatorIndex.name: operatorIndex
operatorIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used for identifying instances of the columnar objects in the operator table.

operatorIdentifier.name: operatorIdentifier
operatorIdentifier.description: A textual string giving the name of this operator. Cannot be empty. A name for a new operator cannot duplicate a name for an existing operator. There is no default value, so a valid value for this column must be includedin any set request for row creation.

operatorPrivilege.name: operatorPrivilege
operatorPrivilege.description: The privilege level for this operator.

dsx1LineType.name: dsx1LineType
dsx1LineType.description: This variable indicates the variety of DS1 Line implementing this circuit. The type of circuit affects the number of bits per second that the circuit can reasonably carry, as well as the interpretation of the usage and error statistics. The values, in sequence, describe: TITLE: SPECIFICATION: dsx1ESF Extended SuperFrame DS1 dsx1D4 AT&T D4 format DS1 dsx1E1 CCITT Recommendation G.704 (Table 4a) dsx1E1-CRC CCITT Recommendation G.704 (Table 4b) dsxE1-MF G.704 (Table 4a) with TS16 multiframing enabled dsx1E1-CRC-MF G.704 (Table 4b) with TS16 multiframing enabled

dsx1LineCoding.name: dsx1LineCoding
dsx1LineCoding.description: This variable describes the variety of Zero Code Suppression used on the link, which in turn affects a number of its characteristics. dsx1B8ZS refers to the use of a specified pat- tern of normal bits and bipolar violations which are used to replace a sequence of eight zero bits. ANSI Clear Channels may use dsx1ZBTSI, or Zero Byte Time Slot Interchange. E1 links, with or without CRC, use dsx1HDB3 or dsx1AMI. dsx1AMI refers to a mode wherein no zero code suppression is present and the line encoding does not solve the problem directly. In this application, the higher layer must provide data which meets or exceeds the pulse density re- quirements, such as inverting HDLC data.

dsx1SendCode.name: dsx1SendCode
dsx1SendCode.description: This variable indicates what type of code is being sent across the DS1 interface by the dev- ice. The values mean: dsx1SendNoCode sending looped or normal data dsx1SendLineCode sending a request for a line loopback dsx1SendPayloadCode sending a request for a payload loopback dsx1SendResetCode sending a loopback termination request dsx1SendQRS sending a Quasi-Random Signal (QRS) test pattern dsx1Send511Pattern sending a 511 bit fixed test pattern dsx1Send3in24Pattern sending a fixed test pattern of 3 bits set in 24 dsx1SendOtherTestPattern sending a test pattern other than those described by this object

dsx1CircuitIdentifier.name: dsx1CircuitIdentifier
dsx1CircuitIdentifier.description: This variable contains the transmission vendor's circuit identifier, for the purpose of facilitating troubleshooting.

dsx1LoopbackConfig.name: dsx1LoopbackConfig
dsx1LoopbackConfig.description: This variable represents the loopback confi- guration of the DS1 interface. Agents support- ing read/write access should return badValue in response to a requested loopback state that the interface does not support. The values mean: dsx1NoLoop Not in the loopback state. A device that is not capable of performing a loopback on the interface shall always return this as it's value. dsx1PayloadLoop The received signal at this interface is looped through the device. Typically the received signal is looped back for re- transmission after it has passed through the device's framing function. dsx1LineLoop The received signal at this interface does not go through the device (minimum pene- tration) but is looped back out. dsx1OtherLoop Loopbacks that are not defined here.

dsx1LineStatus.name: dsx1LineStatus
dsx1LineStatus.description: This variable indicates the Line Status of the interface. It contains loopback, failure, re- ceived 'alarm' and transmitted 'alarm' infor- mation. -- The dsx1LineStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, -- therefore, it can represent multiple failures (alarms) and -- a LoopbackState simultaneously. -- dsx1NoAlarm should be set if and only if no other flag is -- set. -- If the dsx1LoopbackState bit is set, the loopback in ef- -- fect can be determined from the dsx1LoopbackConfig object. -- The various bit positions are: -- 1 dsx1NoAlarm No Alarm Present -- 2 dsx1RcvFarEndLOF Far end LOF (a.k.a. Yellow Alarm) -- 4 dsx1XmtFarEndLOF Near end sending LOF Indication -- 8 dsx1RcvAIS Far end sending AIS -- 16 dsx1XmtAIS Near end sending AIS -- 32 dsx1LossOfFrame Near end LOF (a.k.a. Red Alarm) -- 64 dsx1LossOfSignal Near end Loss Of Signal -- 128 dsx1LoopbackState Near end is looped -- 256 dsx1T16AIS E1 TS16 AIS -- 512 dsx1RcvFarEndLOMF Far End Sending TS16 LOMF -- 1024 dsx1XmtFarEndLOMF Near End Sending TS16 LOMF -- 2048 dsx1RcvTestCode Near End detects a test code -- 4096 dsx1OtherFailure any line status not defined here

dsx1LineMode.name: dsx1LineMode
dsx1LineMode.description: This set of values describes the mode of the WAN I/F. For DS1 lines it sets the mode to CSU by way of a standard dB level, and for DSX configurations sets the line buildout in feet. for E1 lines, it sets the mode in Ohm

dsx1TransmitClockSource.name: dsx1TransmitClockSource
dsx1TransmitClockSource.description: The source of Tranmit Clock. 'loopTiming' indicates that the recovered re- ceive clock is used as the transmit clock. 'localTiming' indicates that a local clock source is used. 'throughTiming' indicates that recovered re- ceive clock from another interface is ised as the transmit clock.

dsx1Fdl.name: dsx1Fdl
dsx1Fdl.description: This bitmap describes the use of the facili- ties data link, and is the sum of the capabili- ties: 'other' indicates that a protocol other than one following is used. 'dsx1Ansi-T1-403' refers to the FDL exchange recommended by ANSI. (This is a T1-only option.) 'dsx1Att-54016' refers to ESF FDL exchanges. (This is a T1-only option.) 'dsx1Fdl-none' indicates that the device does not use the FDL.
